{{About|Russian businessman|Russian soccer player|Andrei Akimov (footballer)}}
'''Andrey Igorevich Akimov''' (in {{lang-ru|Андрей Игоревич Акимов}}, born 1953 in [[Leningrad]], [[Soviet Union]]) is the Chairman of the Management Board of [[Gazprombank]] (open [[joint-stock company]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazprom.ru/about/management/directors/akimov/|title=Andrey I. Akimov|language=Russian|accessdate=18 January 2013}}</ref>
==Early life and education== Akimov was born in [[Leningrad]] in 1953. He earned his degree from the [[Financial University under the Government of the Russian Federation|Moscow Financial Institute]] in 1975, studying international economics, finance and banking.<ref name=":0">{{cite web|title=Andrei Akimov |url=http://www.russiancapitalistwiki.com/wiki/Andrei_Akimov |publisher=Russian Capitalist Wiki |accessdate=11 November 2013 |author=Russian Capitalist Wiki contributors |date=8 November 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131112075832/http://www.russiancapitalistwiki.com/wiki/Andrei_Akimov |archivedate=12 November 2013 }}</ref>
==Career==
===Vneshtorgbank=== From 1974 to 1987, Andrey Akimov was employed in [[Vneshtorgbank]] at senior positions. From 1985 to 1987, he held a post of Deputy Director General of the Vneshtorgbank branch in [[Zurich]] ([[Switzerland]]). From 1987 to 1990 he took up a post of Director General of the Soviet-controlled [[Donau Bank]] in [[Vienna]] ([[Austria]]).<ref name=":0" />
===IMAG GmbH=== From January 1991 to November 2002, he was a Managing Director of the financial company IMAG GmbH in Vienna (Austria) as well as a regular advisor to the Chairman of the Management Board of Vneshtorgbank.<ref name=":0" />
===GPB=== In November 2002, Akimov has taken up a post of the Chairman of the Management Board of the GPB (OJSC).<ref name=":0" />
In April 2018, the United States imposed sanctions on him and 23 other Russian nationals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.treasury.gov/resource-center/sanctions/OFAC-Enforcement/Pages/20180406.aspx |title=Ukraine-/Russia-related Designations and Identification Update|author= |date=2018-04-06 |website=[[United States Department of the Treasury]] |publisher= |accessdate=2018-04-06 |language=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://meduza.io/news/2018/04/06/ssha-vveli-sanktsii-protiv-36-rossiyskih-biznesmenov |title=США ввели санкции против семи российских олигархов и 17 чиновников из «кремлевского списка» |trans-title=The US imposed sanctions against seven Russian oligarchs and 17 officials from the "Kremlin list" |author= |date=2018-04-06 |website=[[Meduza]] |publisher= |accessdate=2018-04-06 |language=ru}}</ref>
==Corporate boards== Since December 2006, Akimov is a member of the [[Novatek]] Board of Directors. Since June 2011, he is a member of the [[Gazprom]] Board of Directors.<ref name=":0" /> ==References== {{Reflist}}
