{{Notability|Biography|date=September 2010}}
'''Brett Arends''', born in [[Poughkeepsie, New York]], is an American writer and journalist. Since 2007, Arends has been a columnist for the ''[[Wall Street Journal]]'' (WSJ) and other [[Dow Jones|Dow Jones publications]], such as [[MarketWatch]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Topics - Brett Arends|url=http://www.marketwatch.com/topics/Journalists/brett-arends|website=MarketWatch|accessdate=10 June 2017|language=en}}</ref> He was a contributing editor and wrote a weekly column for WSJ's personal finance magazine, ''[[SmartMoney]]'', until it closed in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=Brett Arends|url=http://www.smartmoney.com/columnist/brett_arends/|website=SmartMoney|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121223104603/http://www.smartmoney.com/columnist/brett_arends/#|archivedate=2012-12-23|access-date=2012-10-14|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref> He now writes for the Wall Street Journal's online edition's R.O.I. or Return on Investment, daily.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/news/author/1246|title=Brett Arends - News, Articles, Biography, Photos  - WSJ.com|website=WSJ|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref>

Prior to joining WSJ, Arends was a columnist and reporter for the ''[[Boston Herald]]'' and [[TheStreet.com]], a financial [[news agency|news service]].<ref name="Cramer2007">{{cite book|author= James J. Cramer|title=Jim Cramer's Stay Mad for Life: Get Rich, Stay Rich (Make Your Kids Even Richer)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=l6-GkHUu5qwC&pg=PA35|date=4 December 2007|publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn=978-1-4165-7740-9|lccn=2007037828|page=35}}</ref> He has also written for ''[[Private Eye]]'' and the ''[[Daily Mail]]'' in London. He is a former analyst and consultant for the [[McKinsey & Co.]], a [[management consulting]] firm. He took a "double first" in History at [[Cambridge]], and received his master's degree from [[Oxford University|Oxford]] University.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://talkingbiznews.com/1/arends-to-join-smartmoney/|title=Arends joins SmartMoney - Talking Biz News|date=13 February 2012|author=Chris Roush|website=talkingbiznews.com|accessdate=9 July 2017}}</ref>

In 2012, Arends received a Best in Business Journalism award from the [[Society of American Business Editors and Writers]] (SABEW) for his columns in TheStreet.com.<ref>{{cite web|author1=The Society of American Business Editors and Writers|title=SABEW Announces Winners in Its 13th Annual Best in Business Journalism Contest|url=http://www2.prnewswire.com/cgi-bin/stories.pl?ACCT=109&STORY=/www/story/03-27-2008/0004781478&EDATE=|website=PR Newswire|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314142724/http://www2.prnewswire.com/cgi-bin/stories.pl?ACCT=109&STORY=%2Fwww%2Fstory%2F03-27-2008%2F0004781478&EDATE=#|archivedate=2012-03-14|access-date=2017-07-25|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> He was also part of a ''Boston Herald'' team that won two SABEW awards in 2006. He has appeared on ''[[60&nbsp;Minutes]]'',<ref>{{cite web|title=Sticker shock: Why are glasses so expensive?|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/luxottica-eyewear-why-are-glasses-expensive/|website=60 Minutes|publisher=CBS News|accessdate=10 June 2017|date=15 June 2014}}</ref> ''[[PBS NewsHour]]'' with [[Jim Lehrer]], CNBC, MSNBC, CNN, ''[[The John Batchelor Show]]'', and many other radio and TV programs.{{citation needed|date=June 2017}}

Arends' publications include:
*{{cite book|title=The Romney Files: From Bain to Boston to the White House Bid|date=2012|publisher=CreateSpace Independent Publishing Platform|isbn=9781479100910}} — A biography of Republican presidential nominee [[Mitt Romney]]<ref>{{cite news|author=Matt Taibbi|title=Greed and Debt: The True Story of Mitt Romney and Bain Capital|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/politics/news/greed-and-debt-the-true-story-of-mitt-romney-and-bain-capital-20120829?page=3|accessdate=10 June 2017|work=Rolling Stone|date=29 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=The Romney Files: From Bain to Boston to the White House Bid|year=2012|publisher=CreateSpace Independent Publishing Platform|isbn=9781479100910|url=https://www.amazon.com/The-Romney-Files-Boston-White/dp/1479100919/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1350255210&sr=8-1&keywords=the+romney+files}}</ref>
*{{cite book|title=Storm Proof Your Money: Weather Any Economy, Rebuild Your Portfolio, Protect Your Future|isbn=978-0-470-48268-1|publisher=Wiley|date=2009}} — A book about [[personal finance]]<ref>{{cite book|title=Storm Proof Your Money: Weather Any Economy, Rebuild Your Portfolio, Protect Your Future|isbn=978-0-470-48268-1|publisher=Wiley|url=http://www.wiley.com/WileyCDA/WileyTitle/productCd-0470482680.html|accessdate=10 June 2017|date=2009}}</ref>
*{{cite book|title=Spread Betting: The Football Fan's Guide to Spread Betting|year=2002|publisher=Little, Brown Book Group|isbn=9780751534115}} — A book about [[sports gambling]]<ref>{{cite book|title=Spread Betting: The Football Fan's Guide to Spread Betting|date=2002|publisher=Little, Brown Book Group|isbn=9780751534115}}</ref>

